<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 31 at 4:20PM EDT  by NWS Tallahassee</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Berrien and northern
Lanier Counties through 515 PM EDT...
At 420 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Pearson, moving west at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Nashville, Lakeland, Enigma, Ray City, Alapaha, Meigs, Courthouse,
Cottle, Berrien Co A/P, New Lois, Glory, Bannockburn, Allenville,
Weber and Teeterville.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
